"***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre?\"***\n1. Not very likely\n\nBond has been caught by Le Chiffre and his two gunmen, and he has been disarmed. He is being held captive, and it seems unlikely that he will be able to escape in the immediate future.\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"***\n6. Very suspenseful\n\nThe passage is suspenseful because Bond is in a desperate situation, and the outcome is uncertain. He has been caught and disarmed, and it is unclear what will happen to him next. The use of action-packed language, such as \"With a backward kick which connected with the thin man's shins\" and \"he crashed to the ground\", adds to the suspense.\n\nQuestion 1: 1. Not very likely\nQuestion 2: 6. Very suspenseful"